{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "name": "Aegis Backend Test",
    "description": "Simulates a backend service that:\n1. Logs in to **Aegis** (same flow as aegis-admin-ui)\n2. Uses the resulting **Keycloak JWT** to consume endpoints on both **Aegis** and **aegis-admin**\n3. Validates incoming Keycloak JWTs for its own protected resources\n\n## Flow\n\n```\nGET /login\n  → GET  {aegis}/api/v1/auth/encryption-key       (fetch RSA JWK)\n  → encrypt { credentials: {pass, user_check}, anti_replay } with JWE (RSA-OAEP-256 / A256GCM)\n  → POST {aegis}/api/v1/auth/{country}/admin/login (Keycloak JWT returned)\n\nGET /admin/*     → proxied to aegis-admin using cached token\nGET /resource/*  → this backend validates the token you pass as Bearer\n```\n\n## Environment variables needed\n- `local_base_url`    — this test server (default `http://localhost:3000`)\n- `aegis_base_url`   — Aegis Core URL\n- `aegis_admin_url`  — aegis-admin URL\n- `token`            — filled automatically by the Login request",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [ 
    {
      "name": "1 · Login",
      "_postman_id": "f1000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
      "description": "Full login flow identical to aegis-admin-ui:\n1. Fetch RSA JWK from Aegis\n2. Encrypt credentials as JWE (RSA-OAEP-256 / A256GCM)\n3. POST to Aegis admin/login\n4. Returns a Keycloak-issued JWT\n\nThe test script saves the token to {{token}}.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login",
          "_postman_id": "f1000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000002",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{local_base_url}}/login",
              "host": ["{{local_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["login"]
            },
            "description": "Calls internally:\n  GET  {{aegis_base_url}}/api/v1/auth/encryption-key\n  POST {{aegis_base_url}}/api/v1/auth/{{aegis_country}}/admin/login\n\nReturns the raw Keycloak JWT and its decoded payload."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "try {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    const token = json.token;",
                  "    if (token) {",
                  "        pm.environment.set('token', token);",
                  "        const p = json.jwtPayload ?? {};",
                  "        console.log('Token saved. username:', p.preferred_username, '| roles:', p.realm_access?.roles);",
                  "        pm.test('Login OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "        pm.test('Token received', () => pm.expect(token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
                  "    } else {",
                  "        pm.test('Token received', () => pm.expect.fail('token missing — check AEGIS_USERNAME / AEGIS_PASSWORD in .env'));",
                  "    }",
                  "} catch (e) { console.error(e.message); }"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Aegis — Encryption Key",
          "_postman_id": "f1000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000003",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{local_base_url}}/aegis/encryption-key",
              "host": ["{{local_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["aegis", "encryption-key"]
            },
            "description": "Proxies: GET {{aegis_base_url}}/api/v1/auth/encryption-key\nReturns the RSA JWK used to encrypt the login password."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "2 · aegis-admin resources",
      "_postman_id": "f2000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
      "description": "Proxied calls to aegis-admin. The backend uses the cached Keycloak JWT automatically — no Bearer header needed here.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Services — list",
          "_postman_id": "f2000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000002",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{local_base_url}}/admin/services?page=1&take=10",
              "host": ["{{local_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["admin", "services"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "page", "value": "1" },
                { "key": "take", "value": "10" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Proxies: GET {{aegis_admin_url}}/api/v1/services"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Not 401', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.not.equal(401));",
                  "pm.test('Not 403', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.not.equal(403));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Services — detail",
          "_postman_id": "f2000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000003",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{local_base_url}}/admin/services/:id",
              "host": ["{{local_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["admin", "services", ":id"],
              "variable": [{ "key": "id", "value": "" }]
            },
            "description": "Proxies: GET {{aegis_admin_url}}/api/v1/services/:id"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Clients — list",
          "_postman_id": "f2000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000004",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{local_base_url}}/admin/clients",
              "host": ["{{local_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["admin", "clients"]
            },
            "description": "Proxies: GET {{aegis_admin_url}}/api/v1/admin/clients"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Clients — sessions",
          "_postman_id": "f2000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000005",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{local_base_url}}/admin/clients/:clientId/sessions",
              "host": ["{{local_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["admin", "clients", ":clientId", "sessions"],
              "variable": [{ "key": "clientId", "value": "" }]
            },
            "description": "Proxies: GET {{aegis_admin_url}}/api/v1/admin/clients/:clientId/sessions"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Realm — sessions",
          "_postman_id": "f2000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000006",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{local_base_url}}/admin/realms/:realm/sessions?page=1&take=10",
              "host": ["{{local_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["admin", "realms", ":realm", "sessions"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "page", "value": "1" },
                { "key": "take", "value": "10" }
              ],
              "variable": [{ "key": "realm", "value": "puntored-co" }]
            },
            "description": "Proxies: GET {{aegis_admin_url}}/api/v1/admin/realms/:realm/sessions"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "3 · JWT validation (resource server)",
      "_postman_id": "f3000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
      "description": "This backend acts as a resource server that validates the Keycloak JWT you send.\nUse the token from step 1 as Bearer.\n\nJWKS is fetched automatically from {iss}/protocol/openid-connect/certs.",
      "auth": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "bearer": [
          { "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }
        ]
      },
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Public resource (no token)",
          "_postman_id": "f3000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000002",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{local_base_url}}/resource/public",
              "host": ["{{local_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["resource", "public"]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Protected (signature only)",
          "_postman_id": "f3000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000003",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{local_base_url}}/resource/protected",
              "host": ["{{local_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["resource", "protected"]
            },
            "description": "Validates RS256 signature via Keycloak JWKS + expiry.\nNo role check — any valid Keycloak JWT grants access.\n\n→ 200  valid token\n→ 401  missing/invalid/expired token"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Access granted', () => pm.expect(json.message).to.include('granted'));",
                  "pm.test('JWT claims returned', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.jwt).to.have.property('sub');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.jwt).to.have.property('roles');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Admin resource (role: aegis-admin)",
          "_postman_id": "f3000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000004",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{local_base_url}}/resource/admin",
              "host": ["{{local_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["resource", "admin"]
            },
            "description": "Validates signature + checks realm_access.roles[] contains 'aegis-admin'.\n\n→ 200  valid token + role present\n→ 403  valid token but role missing"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Access granted', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.include('granted'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Role check — aegis-writer",
          "_postman_id": "f3000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000005",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{local_base_url}}/resource/role/aegis-writer",
              "host": ["{{local_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["resource", "role", "aegis-writer"]
            },
            "description": "Dynamic role check. Replace last segment with any role from realm_access.roles."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Role check — ADMIN",
          "_postman_id": "f3000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000006",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{local_base_url}}/resource/role/ADMIN",
              "host": ["{{local_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["resource", "role", "ADMIN"]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "4 · Negative Tests",
      "_postman_id": "f4000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
      "description": "Verify the backend correctly rejects bad tokens.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "No token → 401",
          "_postman_id": "f4000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000002",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{local_base_url}}/resource/protected",
              "host": ["{{local_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["resource", "protected"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 401', () => pm.response.to.have.status(401));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Tampered token → 401",
          "_postman_id": "f4000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000003",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiJ9.eyJzdWIiOiJmYWtlIiwiaXNzIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9mYWtlLmlzc3Vlci5jbyJ9.invalidsig" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{local_base_url}}/resource/protected",
              "host": ["{{local_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["resource", "protected"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 401', () => pm.response.to.have.status(401));",
                  "pm.test('JWT validation failed', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().error).to.include('JWT validation failed'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Valid token, missing role → 403",
          "_postman_id": "f4000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000004",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{local_base_url}}/resource/role/super-secret-role",
              "host": ["{{local_base_url}}"],
              "path": ["resource", "role", "super-secret-role"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 403', () => pm.response.to.have.status(403));",
                  "pm.test('token_roles listed', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().token_roles).to.be.an('array'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
